 leaves after recording \"Ain't No Nice Guy\" for the ''[[March \u00f6r Die|March or Die]]'' album. The drummer on that album is Tommy Aldridge, who was replaced by Mikkey Dee after recording the album.\n*[[Metallica]] frontman [[James Hetfield]] suffers second and third-degree burns due to a pyrotechnic accident during the [[Guns N' Roses/Metallica Stadium Tour]].<ref>{{cite web|title=25 Years Ago: A Guns N' Roses and Metallica Concert Ends in a Riot|url=http://ultimateclassicrock.com/guns-n-roses-1992-montreal-riot/|website=Ultimate Classic Rock|accessdate=11 May 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[Living Colour]]'s bassist [[Muzz Skillings]] leaves and is replaced by [[Doug Wimbish]].\n* On April, 20, [[The Freddie Mercury Tribute Concert]] is held. Top heavy metal/hard rock acts such as [[Guns N' Roses]], [[Def Leppard]], [[Metallica]], [[Extreme (band)|Extreme]] and the heavy metal parody band [[Spinal Tap (band)|Spinal Tap]] perform, as well as heavy metal/hard rock legends such as [[Robert Plant]] ([[Led Zeppelin]]), [[Roger Daltrey]] ([[The Who]]), and [[Tony Iommi]] ([[Black Sabbath]]).\n* [[Body Count (band)|Body Count]] sparks nationwide controversy over the song from their [[Body Count (album)|self-titled debut album]], \"[[Cop Killer (song)|Cop Killer]]\".\n* [[Vince Neil]] leaves [[M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce]] and is replaced by [[John Corabi]]\n* [[Slayer]] drummer [[Dave Lombardo]] is replaced by [[Paul Bostaph]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Slayer draft in Paul Bostaph to replace drummer Dave Lombardo - NME|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/slayer-13-1253991|website=NME|accessdate=11 May 2018|date=3 June 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Fanoft Stave Church]] near [[Bergen]], [[Norway]] is destroyed by [[Varg Vikernes]] of [[Burzum]] on June 6. Other church burnings attributed to [[black metal]] [[Early Norwegian black metal scene|musicians]] also took place throughout Scandinavia.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Timeline box|title=[[Timeline of heavy metal music|Heavy Metal Timeline]]|before=[[1991 in heavy metal music|1991]]|after=[[1993 in heavy metal music|1993]]|year='''1992'''}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Timeline of heavy metal and hard rock music}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1992 In Heavy Metal Music}}\n[[Category:1990s in heavy metal music]]\n[[Category:1992 in music|Metal]]\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=September 2017}}\n{{Year in music|1992}}\n{{Year nav topic5|1992|heavy metal music}}\n\nThis is a timeline documenting the events of [[Heavy Metal music|heavy metal]] in the year 1992.\n\n==Newly formed bands==\n*[[Ancient (band)|Ancient]] \n*[[Boris (band)|Boris]] \n*[[Callenish Circle]]\n*[[Carpathian Forest]]\n*[[Cephalic Carnage]]\n* [[Cruachan (band)|Cruachan]]\n*[[Dew-Scented]]\n*[[Dies Irae (band)|Dies Irae]]\n*[[Disciple (band)|Disciple]] \n*[[Disgorge (American band)|Disgorge]] \n* [[Edguy]]\n* [[Esoteric (band)|Esoteric]]\n* [[Evoken]]\n*[[Fight (band)|Fight]] \n* [[Freak Kitchen]]\n*[[Gates of Ishtar]]\n*[[Godgory]]\n* [[Gorgoroth]]\n* [[Graveworm]]\n*[[Judas Iscariot (band)|Judas Iscariot]]\n* [[Legion of the Damned (band)|Legion of the Damned]] (as Occult)\n*[[Lord Belial]]\n* [[Lordi]]\n*[[Memento Mori (band)|Memento Mori]]\n*[[Moonspell]]\n*[[Naglfar (band)|Naglfar]] \n*[[Nasum]]\n* [[Necrophagist]]\n* [[P.O.D.]]\n* [[Rudra (band)|Rudra]]\n*[[Sirrah (band)|Sirrah]] \n*[[Skinless]]\n* [[Stone Sour]]\n*[[The Chasm (band)|The Chasm]] \n* [[Vince Neil]]\n* [[Wolfgang (band)|Wolfgang]]\n\n==Reformed bands==\n* [[Mercyful Fate]]\n\n==Albums==\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[24-7 Spyz]] \u2013 ''[[Strength in Numbers (24-7 Spyz album)|Strength in Numbers]]''\n* [[AC/DC]] \u2013 ''[[AC/DC Live]]'' (live)\n* [[Alice in Chains]] \u2013 ''[[Dirt (Alice in Chains album)|Dirt]]''\n* Alice in Chains \u2013 ''[[Sap (album)|Sap]]'' (EP)\n* [[Amorphis]] - ''[[The Karelian Isthmus]]''\n* [[Anathema (band)|Anathema]] - ''[[The Crestfallen]]'' (EP)\n* [[Anthem (band)|Anthem]] \u2013 ''Domestic Booty''\n* [[Asphyx]] - ''[[Crush the Cenotaph