{"title_page": "GenZe (company)", "text_new": "{{About|the company|demographic cohort|Generation Z}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Mahindra GenZe\n| logo = GenZe logo.svg\n| trade_name = GenZe\n| former_name = \n| type = [[Subsidiary]]\n| industry = [[Electric bicycle]]s and [[Electric motorcycles and scooters|scooters]]\n| founded = \n| founder = \n| hq_location_city = [[Fremont, California|Fremont]], [[California]]\n| hq_location_country = [[United States|U.S.]]\n| area_served = \n| key_people = \n| products = \n| parent = [[Mahindra Group]]\n| website = {{URL|https://www.genze.com}}\n}}\n[[File:GenZe Electric Scooter 2.0s - June 2018 (2007).jpg|thumb|GenZe 2.0s Electric Scooter sold to consumers with a K-Max 30 [[top-box]]]]\n'''Mahindra GenZe''', doing business as '''GenZe''' and also known as '''GenZe by Mahindra''', is a brand of [[electric bicycle]]s and [[Electric motorcycles and scooters|scooters]]. It is a subsidiary of the [[Mahindra Group]] of India.\n\n== History ==\nIn 2013, GenZe introduced their first electric bicycle and electric scooter.<ref name=\"cleantech717\">{{Cite news|url=https://cleantechnica.com/2017/07/18/genze-e-scooter-partners-postmates/|title=GenZe E-Scooter Partners With Postmates|work=CleanTechnica|language=en-US|access-date=2018-05-17}}</ref> The name GenZe is short for Generation Zero Emissions, which is a reference to their products being [[zero-emissions vehicle]]s.<ref name=\"hansindia1017\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Auto-/2017-10-23/Mahindra-GenZe-India-launch-likely-in-2019/334645|title=Mahindra GenZe India launch likely in 2019|website=The Hans India|language=en|access-date=2018-05-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://auto.ndtv.com/news/auto-expo-2016-mahindra-genze-2-0-electric-scooter-showcased-1273000|title=Auto Expo 2016: Mahindra GenZe 2.0 Electric Scooter Showcased - NDTV CarAndBike|work=CarAndBike|access-date=2018-05-17|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Operations ==\nGenZe operates as a subsidiary of the [[Mahindra Group]].<ref name=\"cnet1017\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnet.com/products/genze-e202-electric-bicycle/preview/|title=Lazy as you want to be: New GenZe e-bike pedals for you|date=2017-10-30|work=CNET|access-date=2018-05-17|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"finex1017\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/auto/bike-news/mahindra-genze-electric-two-wheelers-considered-for-india-might-debut-in-2019/900023/|title=Mahindra GenZe electric two-wheelers considered for India, might debut in 2019|date=2017-10-20|work=The Financial Express|access-date=2018-05-17|language=en-US}}</ref> Its headquarters are located in [[Fremont, California]].<ref name=\"finex1017\" /><ref name=\"cab418\">{{Cite news|url=https://auto.ndtv.com/news/ford-and-mahindra-genze-collaborate-for-gobike-electric-bicycle-in-san-francisco-1839461|title=Ford And Mahindra Genze Collaborate For GoBike Electric Bicycle In San Francisco - NDTV CarAndBike|work=CarAndBike|access-date=2018-05-17|language=en}}</ref> GenZe's products are manufactured, hand-assembled, and road-tested in [[Ann Arbor, Michigan]].<ref name=\"finex1017\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://auto.ndtv.com/videos/mahindra-genze-electric-scooter-first-look-483995|title=Mahindra Genze Electric Scooter First Look|website=CarAndBike|language=en|access-date=2018-05-17}}</ref><ref name=\"detnews1117\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.detroitnews.com/story/business/autos/foreign/2017/11/03/india-carmaker-plans-auburn-hills-auto-plant/107314130/|title=First in 25 years: Automaker plans Detroit area plant|work=Detroit News|access-date=2018-05-17|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"industryweek717\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.industryweek.com/global-economy/mahindra-plans-double-investment-us|title=Mahindra Plans to Double Investment in US|date=2017-07-24|work=IndustryWeek|access-date=2018-05-17}}</ref>\n\n== Products ==\n[[File:Scoot in San Francisco - May 2018 (1300).jpg|thumb|GenZe 2.0 Electric Scooter utilized by Scoot Network fleet|left]]\nGenZe designs and manufactures [[electric bicycle]]s and [[Electric motorcycles and scooters|electric scooters]] intended for consumers and corporate fleets.<ref name=\"hansindia1017\" /><ref name=\"cnet1017\" /><ref name=\"engadget518\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.engadget.com/2017/11/10/genze-commuter-ebike-review/|title=GenZe has a commuter e-bike for a connected world|work=Engadget|access-date=2018-05-17|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n=== Electric bicycles ===\nTheir electric bicycles are available through the [[Ford GoBike]] public bicycle sharing system,<ref name=\"cab418\" /> and the Bike Solar Oakland program in [[Oakland, California]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.greenbiz.com/article/mahindra-and-oakland-make-bet-urban-mobility-genze|title=Mahindra and Oakland make a bet on urban mobility with the GenZe|last=Grady|first=Barbara|date=2016-01-19|work=GreenBiz|access-date=2018-05-17|language=en}}</ref>\n\n=== Electric scooters ===\nThe GenZe electric scooters were introduced in 2015,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.kuwaittimes.net/website/indias-largest-suv-maker-rides-into-us-on-a-scooter-electric-scooter-market-to-grow-20000-by-2024/|title=India\u2019s largest SUV maker rides into US on a scooter - Electric scooter market to grow 20,000 by 2024 - Kuwait Times|date=2015-09-02|work=Kuwait Times|access-date=2018-05-21|language=en-US}}</ref> and were delivered to consumers in December 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.genze.com/genze-2-0s-are-on-the-road/|title=GenZe 2.0s Are On The Road! - GenZe|date=2015-12-17|work=GenZe|access-date=2018-05-21|language=en-US}}</ref> They are utilized by [[Postmates]] delivery service.<ref name=\"cleantech717\" /><ref name=\"industryweek717\" /> They are also available through the [[Scoot Networks]] public scooter sharing system,<ref name=\"cleantech717\" /> which the Mahindra Group's private-equity business has invested in.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/opinion/racing-down-new-roads/article9935184.ece|title=Racing down new roads|work=@businessline|access-date=2018-05-17|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/expert-view/happy-to-see-government-creating-aspiration-for-electric-mobility-anand-mahindra/articleshow/62960701.cms|title=Government creating aspiration for electric mobility: Anand Mahindra|date=2018-02-17|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2018-05-17}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Companies|Sports|Transport}}\n* [[List of electric bicycle brands and manufacturers]]\n* [[Outline of cycling]]\n* [[Mahindra Two Wheelers]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.genze.com}}\n\n{{Mahindra Group}}\n\n[[Category:Mahindra Group]]\n[[Category:Scooter manufacturers]]\n[[Category:Manufacturing companies based in California]]\n[[Category:Electric scooters]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Fremont, California]]\n[[Category:Cycle manufacturers of the United States]]\n[[Category:Cycle types]]\n[[Category:Electric vehicles|Bicycle]]\n[[Category:Electric bicycles]]\n[[Category:History of cycling]]\n[[Category:Micromobility]]\n[[Category:Motorized bicycles|*Electric]]\n[[Category:Road cycles]]\n[[Category:Vehicles]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the company|demographic cohort|Generation Z}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Mahindra GenZe\n| logo = GenZe logo.svg\n| trade_name = GenZe\n| former_name = \n| type = [[Subsidiary]]\n| industry = [[Electric bicycle]]s and [[Electric motorcycles and scooters|scooters]]\n| founded = \n| founder = \n| hq_location_city = [[Fremont, California|Fremont]], [[California]]\n| hq_location_country = [[United States|U.S.]]\n| area_served = \n| key_people = \n| products = \n| parent = [[Mahindra Group]]\n| website = {{URL|https://www.genze.com}}\n}}\n[[File:GenZe Electric Scooter 2.0s - June 2018 (2007).jpg|thumb|GenZe 2.0s Electric Scooter sold to consumers with a K-Max 30 [[top-box]]]]\n'''Mahindra GenZe''', doing